<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 22 at 4:30AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Bitterly Cold Conditions Through 9 AM This Morning...
Bitterly cold temperatures will continue through mid morning,
with early morning temperatures between 5 and 20 degrees below
zero across the Lake George Saratoga region, the Mohawk Valley,
Capital Region, eastern Catskills, Berkshires and southern Vermont.
Although winds will be light to calm, the cold conditions could
result in frostbite to exposed skin and/or hypothermia if
precautions are not taken. Running or even a brisk walk in these
conditions could result in frostbite on exposed skin.
If necessary to venture outdoors this morning, make sure to wear
appropriate clothing, preferably in multiple layers, along with a
hat and gloves.</description>
